      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "Our office and @HSILosAngeles have seized more than $2 million from Expert Wound Care, a Pasadena-based advanced wound care clinic suspected of scamming millions of dollars from Medicare through reimbursements for skin graft substitutes and skin grafts that patients never received.\n\nThis clinic, which does business as St. Victoria Home Care, is engaged in fraud according to a seizure warrant affidavit that federal prosecutors filed today.\n\nThis seizure is part of an ongoing investigation, but we moved quickly to protect taxpayer dollars and return money back to the government.\n\nUnder the leadership of President Trump, @VP Vance, and @DrOzCMS, the federal government is turning off the spigot of taxpayer dollars flowing straight into the bank accounts of criminals.",
      "text_resolved": "Our office and @HSILosAngeles have seized more than $2 million from Expert Wound Care, a Pasadena-based advanced wound care clinic suspected of scamming millions of dollars from Medicare through reimbursements for skin graft substitutes and skin grafts that patients never received.\n\nThis clinic, which does business as St. Victoria Home Care, is engaged in fraud according to a seizure warrant affidavit that federal prosecutors filed today.\n\nThis seizure is part of an ongoing investigation, but we moved quickly to protect taxpayer dollars and return money back to the government.\n\nUnder the leadership of President Trump, @VP Vance, and @DrOzCMS, the federal government is turning off the spigot of taxpayer dollars flowing straight into the bank accounts of criminals.",
